### Astronomy:
- Trans-Neptunian Object (TNO): any object in the solar system that orbits the Sun at a greater average distance than Neptune (i.e., beyond 30 astronomical units, or AU).
- Kuiper Belt Object (KBO): a specific type of TNO that resides within the **Kuiper Belt**, a doughnut-shaped region beyond **Neptune** (roughly 30–55 AU).